        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 1:15PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 115 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Burgaw, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Burgaw, White Stocking, Rocky Point, Maple Hill, Long Creek, Wards
Corner, Murray Town, Ashton, Malpass Corner, St. Helena, Watha, and
Pender Memorial Hospital.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 393 and 408.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Move indoors immediately. Lightning is one of nature's leading
killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder, you are close enough to
be struck by lightning.</instruction>
